CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 7, 1941, pg. 18 reads: "Central Baptist Fetes Its Youthful Pastor And Wife" - Words of praise and commendation flowed like water and were as plentiful as the delicious chicken a la king at the banquet Monday night in Central Baptist Church for the Rev. and Mrs. Cornell E. Talley..Upper center: Part of the huge crowd which attended the Monday night affair...Staff photos by Harris"
TitMainTitle: Large group of women and men seated in wooden folding chairs around tables, with woman wearing light colored dress holding plate of food and standing on right, in Central Baptist Church with fringed banners and crepe paper streamers, for banquet honoring Rev. Talley
